@node Installation "Color to Gray: Installation"

                                  Installation
                                 --------------

- copy the file ColorToGray.pss from drawer plugins2/ to ArtEffect:plugins2/

- copy Color_to_Gray.guide whereever you can retrieve it.

After the next start of ArtEffect2+ the menuentry "Color to Gray VR..." should be
available in Menu Filter/Color.

@endnode

@node Requirements "Color to Gray: Requirements"

                                  Requirements
                                 --------------

- the only thing you need is ArtEffect2+

@endnode

@node Usage "Color to Gray: Usage"

                                     Usage
                                    -------

   The usage is quite easy, after calling the plugin via menu, you will see a
   little window.

   Just below the preview are three sliders:

   They represent the weights of the three colorchannel.
   Their unit is a tenth of a percent.

   As long as "Preserve Luminosity" is checked, the weights are controlled and
   always sum up to 100%. That way you won't loose any shades.

   The two buttons are setting default values for the weights.

   Mathgray equals all channes (Well, green is a little preferred as ever)

   Realgray sets the weights according to the weights used by "grayscale"
            television, that comes closer the human kind of viewing.

@endnode

@node Notes "Color to Gray: Notes"

                                     Notes
                                    -------

 - Color to Gray was written on an Amiga 4000 with Cyberstorm MK1 060 and
   compiled with SAS/C 6.58.

 - This PlugIn has no AREXX-Interface and is not localized nor the documentation
   is avaiable in any other language than english (or whatever this is here).
   That may or may not change in the future.

 - If you are interested in getting the information how long an operation took
   try this: setenv VRPLUGINTIMING 1

@endnode

